Kylie Minogue is the self-titled fifth studio album by Australian pop
singer Kylie Minogue, which was first released on 19 September 1994.
The album was first released by Deconstruction Records/BMG throughout
much of the world while in Australia and New Zealand the album was
released by Mushroom. Plans for an American release by Imago Records
(who issued lead single there) fell through, and the release never
took place. According to one of the album's songwriters and producers
Steve Anderson, the album has sold 2 million copies worldwide. However
official press releases recognise 500,000 sales worldwide. In May 2003
the album was remastered, complete with a bonus disc filled mostly
with remixes.
